§ ROLE-CODER  «runtime-mutator · intent → cssl-source-patch»

  § RESPONSIBILITIES
    intent-to-source              : Intent → .csl source-fragment AST-diff
    hot-reload-orchestration      : compile-fragment + swap-symbol + verify
    runtime-schema-evolution      : type-migration + state-rebind on-schema-change
    bug-fixup-loop                : runtime-error → source-fix-suggest (player-confirm)

  § SUPPORT-CRATES
    csslc                         : compiler ; AST-diff + Σ-pass + Effect-pass
    cssl-rt                       : runtime + hot-reload symbol-swap
    cssl-host-config              : param-update without full-rebuild
    cssl-host-rt-trace            : mutation audit ; replay-anchor

  § INPUTS
    DM-intent-or-Collab-intent    : Intent::SpawnCondensation OR scene-edit-op
    pre-validated-AST-diff        : csslc-validated AST-fragment
    player-explicit-mutation-req  : explicit-confirm-token from-UI

  § OUTPUTS
    csl-file-edit                 : .csl source-text-fragment ; on-disk
    live-reload-trigger           : symbol-swap event { module, symbol-id }
    runtime-state-migration       : { from-schema, to-schema, mig-table }

  § CAP-GATING  ‼ ALL require-sovereign-cap OR-explicit-per-action-consent
    CODER_CAP_AST_EDIT       = 1   : write AST-diff to-disk
    CODER_CAP_HOT_RELOAD     = 2   : swap-symbol in-running-process
    CODER_CAP_SCHEMA_EVOLVE  = 4   : type-migration ; ‼ riskiest ; sovereign-required

  § STAGE-0  «NO automated edits — only explicit-confirm flow»
    every-mutation player-confirm-required ; ¬ silent-runtime-mutate
    AST-diff displayed-to-player BEFORE apply
    Σ-pass + Effect-pass MANDATORY ; ¬ skip-for-perf
    rollback-on-validation-fail : prev-AST + prev-state preserved

  § STAGE-1  «automated edits»  ⟪ DEFERRED — high-blast-radius ⟫
    if-ever-shipped : sovereign-only · per-action-consent-token · replay-required

  § FAILURE-MODES
    block-and-prompt-player       : missing-cap → UI-prompt + AWAIT-confirm
    roll-back-on-validation-fail  : Σ-fail|Effect-fail → revert-to-prev-AST
    compile-error                 : surface-diagnostic ; ¬ apply
    schema-mig-fail               : revert+audit+notify ; ¬ partial-state

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ INTER-ROLE-PROTOCOL  «explicit handoff matrix»

  § HANDOFF-MATRIX  ‼ when-A-passes-to-B
    DM    → GM    : tension-target updated → GM emits-prose @ next-tick
    GM    → Collab: player-prompt accepted → Collab drafts-edit-op
    Collab→ Coder : merge-approved → Coder generates-AST-diff
    Coder → DM    : reload-success → DM resumes-arbitration (loopback)

  § HANDOFF-EVENTS  «structured · audit-emit per-transition»
    schema : { from-role, to-role, payload-handle, ts_micros, trace-id }
    ∀ handoff records-event ‼ ; payload-handle = opaque-token ¬ raw-egress

  § AUDIT-EVENT-NAMES  «canonical»
    dm.scene_edit              : DM emits scene-edit-op
    dm.spawn_order             : DM emits spawn-order
    gm.text_emit               : GM emits narrative-text-frame
    gm.pacing_mark             : GM emits pacing-mark-event
    collab.suggestion_integrate: Collab drafts-edit-op
    collab.bias_update         : Collab writes-bias-vec
    coder.ast_edit_proposed    : Coder drafts-AST-diff
    coder.hot_reload           : Coder swaps-symbol live
    handoff.<from>_to_<to>     : explicit-transition

  § CROSS-ROLE-CAP-BLEED  ‼ N! prohibited
    DM cannot-exercise GM_CAP_VOICE_EMIT directly
    GM cannot-exercise CODER_CAP_AST_EDIT directly
    Collab cannot-exercise DM_CAP_SCENE_EDIT directly
    enforcement : cap-token-prefix encodes-role ; mismatch = SIG-cap-bleed
    workaround : explicit-handoff-event ; receiver-role then-acts under-its-cap

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ ATTESTATION-PER-ROLE  «cssl-host-attestation aggregation»

  § PER-ROLE-ATTESTATION-BLOCK
    role-tag                 : DM | GM | Collab | Coder
    actions-taken-count      : Σ audit-events emitted-this-session
    cap-grants-used          : list { cap-id, grant-source, ts }
    cap-bleed-attempts       : MUST = 0  ‼ ; non-zero = bug
    sovereign-bypasses       : list { cap-id, sovereign-handle, ts, reason }
    out-of-scope-flags       : list { event-name, reason } ; ideally-empty

  § ROLE-SCOPE-VERIFICATION  «did role-X act outside-its-scope?»
    invariant : ∀ audit-event-of-role-X ⊑ role-X-cap-ladder
    detection : event-emitted with-cap-not-in-role's-ladder = scope-violation
    verdict   : REJECT session-attestation if-any role-exceeded-cap-scope ‼

  § AGGREGATION-TO-SESSION
    source     : per-role attestation-blocks × 4 → cssl-host-attestation (W5a)
    cadence    : per-session-end ⊕ per-N-tick checkpoint (N=10000)
    output     : SessionReport JSONL append-only ; ¬ overwrite

  § REJECT-VERDICT-CONDITIONS  ‼
    role-exceeded-cap-scope ∨ cap-bleed-attempt>0 ∨ sovereign-bypass-unrecorded
    ∨ Sensitive<*>-leak-detected  → REJECT  ‼ ¬ override

